This paper is about hardware acceleration of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the energy efficiency and power consumption of the proposed accelerator, which could be categorized under embedded systems (cs.ET) and systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed neural processing element is a key feature of the accelerator, which could be categorized under computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper benchmarks the proposed accelerator using a deep neural network, which could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
